-- U.S. aerospace group sees 6 pct rise in civil aircraft sales in 2015
-- By Alwyn Scott
-- Wed Dec 17, 2014 12:44PM EST
-- None



Dec 17 (Reuters) - U.S. civil aircraft sales are expected to rise 6 percent to $79.76 billion in 2015, down from a growth rate of 8 percent in 2014, the Aerospace Industries Association said on Wednesday.

The Washington, D.C.-based trade group forecast the value of commercial aircraft shipments, which includes jetliners and freight aircraft, to rise 6.3 percent to $61.2 billion in 2015.